cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper discusses a routing scheme for privacy-preserving communication in friend-to-friend overlays, which are commonly used for secure communication. The paper focuses on improving the performance and anonymity of existing F2F overlays. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues such as denial-of-service attacks and anonymity, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a routing scheme based on tree embeddings, which could also place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed algorithm, which could also place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
